    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced red onion</strong> to a bowl, cover with <strong>boiled water </strong>and set aside for later</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-chip-and-tzatziki-pitta-with-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin chips, then add them\u00a0to a baking tray with the <strong>dried oregano</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until crisp</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-chip-and-tzatziki-pitta-with-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Grate <strong>half</strong> the <strong>cucumber</strong> and slice the rest into batons</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped mint </strong>and <strong>grated cucumber</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>tzatziki</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-chip-and-tzatziki-pitta-with-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>sliced red onion</strong> in a sieve and rinse under <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Return to the bowl and add the <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Stir to combine and set aside to pickle \u2013 these are your<strong> quick-pickled onions</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-chip-and-tzatziki-pitta-with-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> halloumi</strong> widthways into 4\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> equal-sized strips</p><p>Then slice each strip in half so you are left with 8\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[16] </span><strong>halloumi sticks</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong>\u00a0olive oil\u00a0</strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halloumi sticks</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until golden</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-chip-and-tzatziki-pitta-with-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chips are almost done, add the <strong>pittas</strong> to the tray</p><p>Return the tray to the oven and cook for 2-3 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-chip-and-tzatziki-pitta-with-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Fill the <strong>warmed pittas</strong> with the <strong>chips</strong>, <strong>golden</strong> <strong>halloumi sticks</strong>, <strong>cucumber batons </strong>and a handful of <strong>baby leaf salad</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>tzatziki</strong> and <strong>quick-pickled onions</strong> then wrap in the<strong> tin foil</strong> to hold it all together \u2013 these are your <strong>halloumi, chip & tzatziki pittas</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/halloumi-chip-and-tzatziki-pitta-with-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>halloumi</strong>,<strong> chip & tzatziki pittas </strong>with any <strong>remaining tzatziki</strong> and <strong>baby leaf salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
